00:31:03,873 --> 00:31:06,373
You know, I saw you on the
opening night of your Juliet.

496
00:31:07,181 --> 00:31:07,910
Did you?

497
00:31:08,113 --> 00:31:10,098
I think it was one of
your best performances.

498
00:31:10,569 --> 00:31:11,295
Yes.

499
00:31:12,175 --> 00:31:14,492
Which play would you prefer
to do more than any other?

500
00:31:15,968 --> 00:31:17,164
One I've never done.

501
00:31:18,177 --> 00:31:19,824
A thing called 'But To Die'.

502
00:31:21,094 --> 00:31:23,073
I'd give anything in
the world to play it.

503
00:31:23,764 --> 00:31:25,543
I wouldn't have to
act it, I could live it.

504
00:31:25,783 --> 00:31:27,563
Why hasn't somebody produced it for you?

505
00:31:27,891 --> 00:31:30,452
With the 'Jinx woman' of the theater?
Don't be silly.

506
00:31:32,693 --> 00:31:34,963
I noticed a very interesting
play on your bookshelves.

507
00:31:35,319 --> 00:31:36,105
Which one?

508
00:31:36,762 --> 00:31:40,142
It's called .. 'Forever Ends At Dawn'.

509
00:31:41,062 --> 00:31:43,750
'Forever Ends At Dawn'?
I don't think I've ever read it.

510
00:31:45,049 --> 00:31:46,293
It's a beautiful last act.

511
00:31:46,756 --> 00:31:48,343
You wouldn't read it to me, would you?

512
00:31:48,700 --> 00:31:51,872
Are you sure you would like to hear it?
- It would be a treat to listen to you.

513
00:31:52,684 --> 00:31:54,435
Well, just the last act then.

514
00:31:56,193 --> 00:31:58,616
The scene of the play
is the French Riviera.

515
00:31:59,533 --> 00:32:01,799
The story is about a man and a woman.

516
00:32:02,537 --> 00:32:05,408
She's not a very nice person.
But a fascinating one.

517
00:32:06,732 --> 00:32:10,310
The man has a wife or a
fiancée, I've forgotten which.

518
00:32:10,741 --> 00:32:12,286
With whom he's very much in love.

519
00:32:13,205 --> 00:32:16,773
He's intrigued by this woman but
quite nobly resists her charms.

520
00:32:19,118 --> 00:32:22,159
Here it is .. 'Forever Ends At Dawn'.

521
00:32:23,143 --> 00:32:25,764
You may find the dialog a bit
awkward in spots but I'll ..

522
00:32:26,285 --> 00:32:29,182
I'll try and make it convincing.
- I've never heard you when you weren't.

523
00:32:29,773 --> 00:32:30,608
Thank you.

524
00:32:32,065 --> 00:32:34,553
This scene takes place in the
woman's room late at night.

525
00:32:35,583 --> 00:32:37,821
The man has to go home
in the morning so he ..

526
00:32:38,250 --> 00:32:39,607
Comes to say goodbye to her.

527
00:32:43,140 --> 00:32:44,269
I'll read from here.

528
00:32:45,729 --> 00:32:46,596
Richard:

529
00:32:47,345 --> 00:32:48,996
'I had to come and say goodbye'.

530
00:32:49,540 --> 00:32:51,299
'And tell you it's been
swell knowing you'.

531
00:32:52,536 --> 00:32:53,220
Joan:

532
00:32:54,670 --> 00:32:57,914
'Well I .. thought that our goodbye
would be different from this'.

533
00:32:59,708 --> 00:33:00,545
Richard:

534
00:33:01,449 --> 00:33:04,067
'Yes, but you see .. there's always ..'

535
00:33:06,027 --> 00:33:06,978
Joan: 'I know'.

536
00:33:07,588 --> 00:33:09,269
'That girl in the back of your heart'.

537
00:33:10,734 --> 00:33:11,444
Joan:

538
00:33:12,314 --> 00:33:14,467
'Her 'forever' lasts until
death do you part'.

539
00:33:15,763 --> 00:33:17,757
'My 'forever' only until dawn'.

540
00:33:20,581 --> 00:33:22,438
'Tomorrow is where
regrets lie, Richard'.

541
00:33:23,485 --> 00:33:25,326
'But there will be no tomorrow for us'.

542
00:33:26,466 --> 00:33:27,579
'Only tonight'.

543
00:33:28,452 --> 00:33:29,992
'Which we steal from no-one'.

544
00:33:31,400 --> 00:33:34,884
'And forget as a dream which
has no part of our normal lives'.

545
00:33:35,862 --> 00:33:38,026
'Over which we had no control'.

546
00:33:39,162 --> 00:33:41,500
'And for which we need
feel no obligation'.

547
00:33:43,833 --> 00:33:45,243
Is that the end of the play?

548
00:33:46,418 --> 00:33:47,279
Almost.

549
00:33:49,456 --> 00:33:50,585
Let's have some music.

550
00:34:03,344 --> 00:34:04,931
You know, you read that beautifully.

551
00:34:14,313 --> 00:34:15,319
Now you know.

552
00:34:17,461 --> 00:34:18,670
I know it won't do.

553
00:34:23,930 --> 00:34:25,799
Where are you going?
- Out for a walk.

554
00:34:26,340 --> 00:34:28,413
In this rain?
- I like walking in the rain.

555
00:34:29,163 --> 00:34:31,623
So do I. I think I'll go too.
- There is only one slicker.

556
00:35:02,203 --> 00:35:03,615
Why don't you go back?

557
00:35:47,825 --> 00:35:50,768
Kidneys and bacon and cornbread
this morning, Mister Don.

558
00:35:51,750 --> 00:35:52,773
That's fine.

559
00:35:54,614 --> 00:35:58,532
Miss Heath not down yet?
- No. I called her 15 minutes ago.

560
00:36:01,980 --> 00:36:03,516
Mrs Williams, would you mind ..?

561
00:36:06,923 --> 00:36:07,922
Good morning.

562
00:36:09,296 --> 00:36:11,439
Do you like the negligee I
borrowed from Mrs Williams?

563
00:36:14,178 --> 00:36:15,082
It's fine.

564
00:36:22,818 --> 00:36:24,164
Rather cruel, aren't you?

565
00:36:25,232 --> 00:36:26,326
Why do you say that?

566
00:36:26,789 --> 00:36:29,217
You might at least have smiled
at me as I came down the stairs.

567
00:36:30,105 --> 00:36:31,404
Even if it were a lie.

568
00:36:32,806 --> 00:36:34,977
I don't think this is any time to lie.

569
00:36:36,689 --> 00:36:38,735
Or to speak the truth or
to say anything, in fact.

570
00:36:40,607 --> 00:36:42,302
Could I pour you some coffee?

571
00:36:43,897 --> 00:36:44,759
Joyce.

572
00:36:45,779 --> 00:36:47,302
I hate loose ends.

573
00:36:47,505 --> 00:36:50,267
They .. they tangle your
life, they trip you up.

574
00:36:52,292 --> 00:36:53,221
Yes, Don.

575
00:36:55,455 --> 00:36:56,622
Well, last night ..

576
00:36:57,552 --> 00:37:00,126
I'm sorry I kissed you
and said the things I did.

577
00:37:02,080 --> 00:37:03,874
How very gallant of you to say so.

578
00:37:04,604 --> 00:37:05,895
No, you don't understand.

579
00:37:06,844 --> 00:37:08,779
You see, I'm engaged to someone.

580
00:37:09,413 --> 00:37:10,498
And you blame me?

581
00:37:11,142 --> 00:37:12,953
No. It was unfair to you too.

582
00:37:14,252 --> 00:37:15,274
You are so very ..

583
00:37:16,215 --> 00:37:18,261
Fascinating. I think it was that ..

584
00:37:18,671 --> 00:37:21,377
The storm and our nearness
that made me lose my senses.

585
00:37:23,212 --> 00:37:25,632
I've got them back this morning
and I'm asking you to forgive me.

586
00:37:26,517 --> 00:37:27,151
And.

587
00:37:27,662 --> 00:37:29,647
For what I'm saying now if I hurt you.

588
00:37:30,097 --> 00:37:30,905
Hurt me?

589
00:37:34,404 --> 00:37:35,382
You delight me.

590
00:37:35,775 --> 00:37:38,570
You have the most amazing lack
of humor of anyone I've ever known.

591
00:37:40,921 --> 00:37:43,225
I shouldn't laugh at you, should I.
But I can't help it.

592
00:37:43,923 --> 00:37:46,283
You were so awkward I almost
laughed in your face at first.

593
00:37:46,572 --> 00:37:48,360
Then it made me sick
to think that anyone ..

594
00:37:48,607 --> 00:37:51,167
Could be stupid enough to be
taken in by a lot of old tricks.

595
00:37:52,079 --> 00:37:53,722
I thought you might at least be amusing.

596
00:37:53,925 --> 00:37:56,499
But you turned out to be dull
and stupid and so afraid.

597
00:37:57,007 --> 00:37:58,022
You needn't be.

598
00:37:58,399 --> 00:38:01,895
I won't hurt your Sunday School
romance or your oh-so-nice career.

599
00:38:02,373 --> 00:38:03,611
Hurt me? Ha.

600
00:38:03,897 --> 00:38:06,035
Get out of here before
you give me hysterics.

601
00:38:41,416 --> 00:38:43,711
Sorry friend, but I think you stop here.

602
00:38:44,362 --> 00:38:47,211
It does seem advisable, doesn't it.
How soon will you have it repaired?

603
00:38:47,503 --> 00:38:49,089
Oh the lumber will be here about noon.

604
00:38:49,292 --> 00:38:51,480
And I think you ought to get
across early this evening.

605
00:38:51,797 --> 00:38:53,561
Too bad you didn't get off last night.

606
00:38:54,518 --> 00:38:55,214
Yeah.

607
00:38:55,879 --> 00:38:58,639
Can one of your men get across and
telephone for me from the other side?

608
00:38:58,902 --> 00:39:01,364
Why, sure.
- Have him call 'Miss Armitage'.

609
00:39:02,073 --> 00:39:04,731
At Austin 9532.

610
00:39:05,710 --> 00:39:08,560
Say Mr Bellows has been delayed and
can't see her until this evening.

611
00:39:09,517 --> 00:39:12,450
And I'd be much obliged if you let
me know the minute I can get across.

612
00:39:12,659 --> 00:39:15,665
I'm up at the old Quinn Farm.
- Okay. The first thing.

613
00:39:41,301 --> 00:39:44,232
[ Crying sounds ]

614
00:39:47,818 --> 00:39:49,665
[ Crying sounds ]

615
00:39:53,606 --> 00:39:55,130
[ Crying sounds ]

616
00:39:57,524 --> 00:39:58,370
Joyce.

617
00:39:59,114 --> 00:39:59,862
Don.

618
00:40:00,690 --> 00:40:03,704
You did come back.
I was praying you would.

619
00:40:04,731 --> 00:40:06,103
I had to. You see ..

620
00:40:07,101 --> 00:40:09,754
It doesn't matter why.
You did, you had to.

621
00:40:10,559 --> 00:40:12,802
You didn't believe what I
said this morning, did you?

622
00:40:13,861 --> 00:40:14,643
Did you?

623
00:40:15,191 --> 00:40:16,797
I guess I had it coming to me.

624
00:40:17,257 --> 00:40:19,027
Oh no, Don. It was a lie.

625
00:40:19,642 --> 00:40:20,988
Let's forget about it.

626
00:40:21,224 --> 00:40:23,313
You can forget that.
But I want you to remember this.

627
00:40:23,885 --> 00:40:26,907
I know you belong to somebody else.
And I don't want you, really I don't.

628
00:40:27,881 --> 00:40:29,361
But last night was mine and ..

629
00:40:30,340 --> 00:40:31,756
And I made it ugly this morning.

630
00:40:32,301 --> 00:40:34,003
I don't want you to
think of it that way.

631
00:40:34,319 --> 00:40:35,048
I won't.

632
00:40:35,885 --> 00:40:37,487
You will, unless I tell you the truth.

633
00:40:38,346 --> 00:40:40,732
You've seen me drunk and disgusting.

634
00:40:41,234 --> 00:40:44,170
You took me in out of pity.
Well, that hurt my pride.

635
00:40:45,223 --> 00:40:48,248
And because I'm a good deal of
a shrew, I wanted to hurt yours.

636
00:40:49,424 --> 00:40:51,524
I was going to tease you
with all the tricks I knew ..

637
00:40:51,727 --> 00:40:53,222
Until you tried to kiss me, and ..

638
00:40:54,068 --> 00:40:55,537
Then I was to laugh in your face.

639
00:40:56,405 --> 00:40:57,891
I was an actress playing a part.

640
00:40:58,561 --> 00:40:59,758
I played it too well.

641
00:41:01,032 --> 00:41:03,883
But when you took me in your
arms .. I didn't want to laugh.

642
00:41:05,059 --> 00:41:06,249
I wanted to cry.

643
00:41:07,566 --> 00:41:09,290
I'm sorry.
- I'm not. I'm glad.

644
00:41:10,419 --> 00:41:11,657
Last night was beautiful.

645
00:41:12,813 --> 00:41:14,181
It will always be beautiful.

646
00:41:15,531 --> 00:41:16,783
And now that it's over.

647
00:41:20,656 --> 00:41:21,808
It's not over, Joyce.

648
00:41:22,655 --> 00:41:24,793
Oh yes, Don. It's got to be over.

649
00:41:26,726 --> 00:41:29,278
Your career is on the verge
of permanent success.

650
00:41:30,137 --> 00:41:32,467
You'll have someone who
can help you. I can't.

651
00:41:33,339 --> 00:41:35,713
I'm the kind of woman
who destroys, not builds.

652
00:41:36,098 --> 00:41:37,366
I'm Joyce Heath, Don.

653
00:41:38,543 --> 00:41:39,693
A Maenad who ..

654
00:41:40,558 --> 00:41:43,433
Who doesn't want to dance over the
cliff with a man as fine as you.

655
00:41:45,439 --> 00:41:48,223
Now come on, let's finish up
the rest of the day very fine.

656
00:41:49,040 --> 00:41:50,505
I'll get dressed. You go down.

657
00:41:58,622 --> 00:41:59,535
I got it.

658
00:42:05,690 --> 00:42:07,206
No, no, Don. That's not fair.

659
00:42:07,705 --> 00:42:10,483
You must be playing by pinochle rules.
- It's just you're slow, that's all.

660
00:42:10,974 --> 00:42:12,013
No wonder.

661
00:42:12,728 --> 00:42:17,033
These cards are so thick and old I could
be playing with Encyclopedia Britannica.

662
00:42:19,442 --> 00:42:20,803
Wait a minute, wait a minute.

663
00:42:21,702 --> 00:42:23,318
The recipe said it was toffee.

664
00:42:24,741 --> 00:42:26,174
But that's not what we've got.

665
00:42:27,012 --> 00:42:28,833
I'll never get my jaws apart.

666
00:42:29,579 --> 00:42:31,310
I'm going to bite the
person that said so.

667
00:42:31,698 --> 00:42:33,911
Pardon me a minute, while
I get out a piece of toffee.

668
00:42:34,196 --> 00:42:36,747
I've lost a couple of molars and
a bicuspid that are sticking to it.

669
00:42:37,327 --> 00:42:39,521
Did you get it?
- Yes, but I think I lost a nail.

670
00:42:40,639 --> 00:42:43,483
Perhaps we should put some sand in that
mess to give it something to hold on to.

671
00:42:45,744 --> 00:42:47,791
I wonder if Mrs Williams
would like some.

672
00:42:48,055 --> 00:42:50,399
It would certainly take the rattle
out her uppers and lowers.

673
00:43:03,183 --> 00:43:04,458
I wish I'd never seen you.

674
00:43:05,408 --> 00:43:07,441
Never kissed you.
Never held you in my arms.

675
00:43:08,854 --> 00:43:11,266
Because every time I do, I hate myself.

676
00:43:11,557 --> 00:43:12,478
I hate you.

677
00:43:13,417 --> 00:43:16,855
I can kill every emotion except the
desire to hold you just once more.

678
00:43:18,817 --> 00:43:20,375
[ Door knocks ]

679
00:43:26,381 --> 00:43:28,917
You can get across the road now, sir.
- Thank you.

680
00:43:29,370 --> 00:43:31,176
I got that phone call
through alright too.

681
00:43:31,552 --> 00:43:33,026
Much obliged. Goodnight.

682
00:43:33,242 --> 00:43:34,059
Goodnight.

683
00:43:40,617 --> 00:43:42,204
You can go now?
- Yes.

684
00:43:43,302 --> 00:43:44,451
Then you must.

685
00:43:45,743 --> 00:43:47,526
Because if you stay,
it will be too late.

686
00:43:48,587 --> 00:43:49,507
I love you.

687
00:43:51,150 --> 00:43:54,684
You may never love me but .. you'll
find you always come back to me.

688
00:43:56,027 --> 00:43:58,928
And each time you return it will
cost you more and more until ..

689
00:43:59,615 --> 00:44:03,545
When you've spent your career,
your ambitions, your dreams.

690
00:44:04,595 --> 00:44:05,802
I am bad for people.

691
00:44:06,572 --> 00:44:08,591
I don't mean to be
but I can't help myself.

692
00:44:10,234 --> 00:44:11,964
So I'm being generous to you, Don.

693
00:44:12,450 --> 00:44:15,154
Kind. Kinder than I've ever
been to anybody before.

694
00:44:16,469 --> 00:44:18,184
But I can't be much longer.

695
00:44:19,424 --> 00:44:20,137
So go.

696
00:44:21,076 --> 00:44:22,090
Leave me.

697
00:44:23,875 --> 00:44:25,382
You can leave me, can't you?

698
00:44:26,854 --> 00:44:27,919
I don't know.

699
00:44:31,492 --> 00:44:32,868
I've got to find out.

700
00:44:42,803 --> 00:44:43,939
Mister Don gone, Miss?

701
00:44:44,662 --> 00:44:45,389
Yes.

702
00:44:46,005 --> 00:44:47,178
He's coming back?

703
00:44:49,836 --> 00:44:51,149
Yes, I think he will.

704
00:44:59,870 --> 00:45:01,114
[ Door knocks ]

705
00:45:01,419 --> 00:45:02,264
Yes?

706
00:45:06,987 --> 00:45:08,940
Mr Bellows.
- Huh?

707
00:45:09,400 --> 00:45:11,077
Miss Armitage is on the telephone.

708
00:45:14,799 --> 00:45:15,723
Put her on.

709
00:45:16,512 --> 00:45:17,098
No.

710
00:45:19,667 --> 00:45:22,008
Tell her I'm still out of town.
I'll call her when I get back.

711
00:45:24,149 --> 00:45:25,285
Very well, sir.

712
00:45:32,182 --> 00:45:36,913
Mr Haynes of United Quarries called many
times to ask if you have a decision.

713
00:45:38,839 --> 00:45:40,823
Tell him I haven't been
able to make up my mind.

714
00:45:41,126 --> 00:45:44,093
He said he'd have to have an answer
one way or the other. Yes or No.

715
00:45:49,736 --> 00:45:50,551
He's right.

716
00:45:52,050 --> 00:45:53,330
It's got to be Yes or No.

717
00:45:55,459 --> 00:45:56,591
Thank you Miss Seals.

718
00:46:08,040 --> 00:46:09,277
[ Door knocks ]

719
00:46:09,880 --> 00:46:10,766
Come in.

720
00:46:11,366 --> 00:46:12,495
Mr Bellows, Miss Gail.

721
00:46:13,333 --> 00:46:13,919
Oh.

722
00:46:14,449 --> 00:46:15,493
Show him in, Betty.

723
00:46:15,943 --> 00:46:18,721
And we'll have coffee.
- Van Houtte for Mr Bellows?

724
00:46:19,130 --> 00:46:20,129
That's right.

725
00:46:27,727 --> 00:46:29,123
Well, hello Mr B.

726
00:46:29,446 --> 00:46:31,062
It's about time you were getting back.

727
00:46:37,981 --> 00:46:40,099
Don .. something has happened?

728
00:46:41,285 --> 00:46:43,183
Yes Gail .. something has happened.

729
00:46:44,257 --> 00:46:46,615
Even if it's all for the
worst, it can't be so bad.

730
00:46:47,118 --> 00:46:49,882
Because you've got the most
enthusiastic assistant in the world.

731
00:46:50,267 --> 00:46:51,535
To help you laugh it off.

732
00:46:51,913 --> 00:46:53,227
Or .. to work it out.

733
00:46:53,798 --> 00:46:55,099
Whichever we're going to do.

734
00:46:56,463 --> 00:46:58,769
Gail, it would make me prouder
to have you as my wife ..

735
00:46:58,972 --> 00:47:00,729
Than to have any other
woman in the world.

736
00:47:02,794 --> 00:47:06,256
If I could respect you a little less, it
would all be very simple, but I can't.

737
00:47:07,029 --> 00:47:08,516
So I must ask you a question.

738
00:47:09,177 --> 00:47:11,077
I'm afraid I know the answer already.

739
00:47:12,249 --> 00:47:13,207
What is it, Don?

740
00:47:15,849 --> 00:47:18,305
If we were married, there is one
humiliation you would never know.

741
00:47:18,538 --> 00:47:20,498
That's having me deceive
you with someone else.

742
00:47:21,256 --> 00:47:23,366
I know that.
- But if there were someone else?

743
00:47:24,132 --> 00:47:27,346
Someone I didn't love, that I'll
never even see again, but who ..

744
00:47:28,576 --> 00:47:32,436
But who had a strange,
exotic fascination for me.

745
00:47:32,669 --> 00:47:34,216
An appeal I couldn't kill.

746
00:47:36,415 --> 00:47:38,122
Would that make any difference to you?

747
00:47:39,134 --> 00:47:40,177
Yes Don, it would.

748
00:47:40,883 --> 00:47:42,928
Whether you ever went to
her or not, wouldn't matter.

749
00:47:43,136 --> 00:47:45,186
But the fact that you'd want to would.

750
00:47:46,448 --> 00:47:49,322
It mightn't make me love
any less .. perhaps more.

751
00:47:50,316 --> 00:47:53,285
The agony of wondering every time you
kiss me whether you're thinking of her.

752
00:47:53,635 --> 00:47:55,621
The hate and dread I'd have
for that other woman.

753
00:47:55,940 --> 00:47:59,222
And the terrific loneliness of that
little part of you which I wouldn't own.

754
00:47:59,883 --> 00:48:01,144
It would be unendurable.

755
00:48:13,891 --> 00:48:17,281
I can't tell you Don, how much I
admire you for .. for being so honest.

756
00:48:18,025 --> 00:48:20,398
And thank you for coming to say goodbye.

757
00:48:21,960 --> 00:48:22,824
You're a ..

758
00:48:26,301 --> 00:48:27,119
Goodbye.

759
00:48:38,030 --> 00:48:40,741
Has Mr Bellows gone, Miss Gail?
Is he coming back?

760
00:48:42,280 --> 00:48:43,032
Yes.

761
00:48:44,646 --> 00:48:45,990
Yes, I think he will.

762
00:48:48,528 --> 00:48:49,535
Mr Sheffield.

763
00:48:49,836 --> 00:48:53,140
I've come to see you for some
advice on producing a play.

764
00:48:53,485 --> 00:48:55,160
That's something I know nothing about.

765
00:48:55,746 --> 00:48:58,359
An angel is a celestial being
after death, Mr Bellows.

766
00:48:58,937 --> 00:49:00,672
But before .. he's a sucker.

767
00:49:01,611 --> 00:49:03,978
Thanks for the warning.
What I want is an opinion.

768
00:49:04,947 --> 00:49:07,215
Have you ever heard of a
play called 'But To Die'?

769
00:49:07,883 --> 00:49:08,984
A magnificent script.

770
00:49:09,588 --> 00:49:11,576
Which with the proper lead
would make a great play.

771
00:49:11,953 --> 00:49:13,605
However, miscast ..

772
00:49:14,018 --> 00:49:17,395
It would close so fast the third act
curtain would snag in the stage door.

773
00:49:18,201 --> 00:49:19,485
Who do you see in the lead?

774
00:49:20,509 --> 00:49:22,056
Only two women could have played it:

775
00:49:22,377 --> 00:49:24,285
Jean Eagles and .. Joyce Heath.

776
00:49:24,578 --> 00:49:26,575
Eagles is dead .. Heath has disappeared.

777
00:49:27,169 --> 00:49:28,070
So, forget it.

778
00:49:28,475 --> 00:49:31,348
If I made both the script and Miss Heath
available to you, would you produce it?

779
00:49:32,316 --> 00:49:34,441
Mr Bellows, I have great
respect for the script.

780
00:49:34,945 --> 00:49:36,889
And almost a reverence
for Miss Heath's talent.

781
00:49:37,565 --> 00:49:40,224
But I wouldn't hazard
$80,000 to defy a jinx.

782
00:49:40,577 --> 00:49:44,187
Surely an intelligent man like you won't
take any stock in a legend like that?

783
00:49:44,459 --> 00:49:46,723
When you ask $80,000 for
a share of it I do.

784
00:49:48,420 --> 00:49:49,963
Suppose I pay the $80,000?

785
00:49:51,796 --> 00:49:53,943
Then I would produce
and direct it myself.

786
00:49:54,942 --> 00:49:56,815
Will you have your lawyer
draw up the contract?

787
00:49:57,766 --> 00:49:58,552
Very well.

788
00:49:59,660 --> 00:50:00,475
By the way.

789
00:50:01,282 --> 00:50:02,612
Do you bite your fingernails?

790
00:50:03,962 --> 00:50:05,607
No.
- You will.

791
00:50:15,344 --> 00:50:16,962
[ Dog barking ]

792
00:50:17,863 --> 00:50:19,057
[ Dog barking ]

793
00:50:50,758 --> 00:50:51,682
You did come.

794
00:50:52,741 --> 00:50:53,799
You knew I would.

795
00:50:56,728 --> 00:50:57,599
Yes, I knew.

796
00:51:06,759 --> 00:51:09,198
Let's go inside, I only have a minute.
I've got to get right back.

797
00:51:09,808 --> 00:51:10,794
Tonight?
- Yeah.

798
00:51:20,272 --> 00:51:21,609
Darling.
- Joyce.

799
00:51:23,975 --> 00:51:25,104
I want to talk to you.

800
00:51:33,361 --> 00:51:34,233
Now listen ..

801
00:51:34,818 --> 00:51:38,088
You and I are both artists.
I deal in permanence. Things that last.

802
00:51:38,591 --> 00:51:41,993
You in emotions, moments, and things
that flame and burn and leave ashes.

803
00:51:42,797 --> 00:51:44,568
So we're not the same. I know that.

804
00:51:45,722 --> 00:51:48,004
But is there any consistency in
the way you feel towards me?

805
00:51:49,371 --> 00:51:50,930
Couldn't we ask questions afterwards?

806
00:51:51,321 --> 00:51:53,774
No .. I can't build without plans.

807
00:51:54,748 --> 00:51:57,743
Answer me, Joyce. Is there consistency
in your feelings towards me?

808
00:52:00,123 --> 00:52:03,465
Tonight I love you so much that nothing
else matters. A love you couldn't kill.

809
00:52:04,749 --> 00:52:05,793
But that's tonight.

810
00:52:07,265 --> 00:52:09,623
Tomorrow should be the same.
I want it to be.

811
00:52:10,779 --> 00:52:13,938
But I've been betrayed so often by
tomorrows, I don't dare promise that.

812
00:52:15,304 --> 00:52:17,292
It's the only honest answer
I can give you darling.

813
00:52:18,180 --> 00:52:19,875
That's a gentleman's answer, Joyce.

814
00:52:20,116 --> 00:52:21,663
I guess I'm not lady enough to lie.

815
00:52:23,600 --> 00:52:24,949
No, I don't think you would.

816
00:52:26,568 --> 00:52:27,762
I broke my engagement.

817
00:52:29,144 --> 00:52:30,790
Why?
- Because of us.

818
00:52:32,389 --> 00:52:33,333
What about her?

819
00:52:33,536 --> 00:52:34,805
Let's leave her out of it.

820
00:52:35,928 --> 00:52:39,255
All I know is, she's stronger than us,
as if she weren't, I wouldn't be here.

821
00:52:40,344 --> 00:52:41,633
And I'm glad I'm weaker.

822
00:52:42,539 --> 00:52:44,098
You are too, aren't you? Say you are.

823
00:52:44,409 --> 00:52:45,255
No, I'm not.

824
00:52:46,269 --> 00:52:47,035
I'm here.

825
00:52:47,786 --> 00:52:49,333
That's all I care about.

826
00:52:49,678 --> 00:52:51,615
There's other things that
are important to me.

827
00:52:52,629 --> 00:52:53,943
First of all, your career.

828
00:52:54,942 --> 00:52:56,770
Why should you concern
yourself about that?

829
00:52:57,213 --> 00:52:59,594
Because you don't belong in
the audience, but on the stage.

830
00:53:00,217 --> 00:53:03,030
Your emotion, your restlessness,
have beauty and poetry there.

831
00:53:03,671 --> 00:53:06,201
Off the stage they'd be brutal.
They would ruin us both.

832
00:53:06,691 --> 00:53:10,946
I hope that in the theater you'll find
enough release to be content with me.

833
00:53:11,817 --> 00:53:14,145
Why should I find contentment?
I don't want it.

834
00:53:14,460 --> 00:53:15,246
Well I do.

835
00:53:15,748 --> 00:53:17,490
I want you and I want peace too.

836
00:53:18,136 --> 00:53:21,003
They wouldn't let me inside a theater.
They'd be afraid it would fall down.

837
00:53:21,818 --> 00:53:25,245
You start rehearsing 'But To Die' for
George Sheffield on Monday morning.

838
00:53:26,203 --> 00:53:26,954
What?

839
00:53:28,246 --> 00:53:28,929
Me?

840
00:53:30,461 --> 00:53:31,565
But To Die?

841
00:53:32,459 --> 00:53:34,272
Oh you're mad.
Sheffield wouldn't risk it.

842
00:53:34,978 --> 00:53:36,548
You get the script from him tomorrow.

843
00:53:37,614 --> 00:53:39,919
Don .. did you put your money in it?

844
00:53:40,137 --> 00:53:40,805
Yes.

845
00:53:41,068 --> 00:53:43,287
Oh you fool .. you crazy fool.

846
00:53:43,652 --> 00:53:44,781
Something will happen.

847
00:53:45,199 --> 00:53:47,009
I've told you a million
times I'm a jinx.

848
00:53:47,558 --> 00:53:49,801
You are no such thing.
You're a great actress.

849
00:53:50,321 --> 00:53:53,966
I'm so sure, I'll risk the money that's
to realize the one ambition I ever had.

850
00:53:54,990 --> 00:53:56,521
You'll be better than you ever were.

851
00:53:56,724 --> 00:53:59,564
If I'm going to marry Joyce Heath,
it's got to be the <i>real</i> Joyce Heath.

852
00:54:07,611 --> 00:54:08,283
Marry?

853
00:54:08,648 --> 00:54:09,294
Yes.

854
00:54:09,737 --> 00:54:12,162
I can't compromise, and I
won't sneak and apologize.

855
00:54:13,289 --> 00:54:15,695
I'm playing you a game but
I'm playing it for keeps.

856
00:54:18,894 --> 00:54:19,943
What's the matter?

857
00:54:23,021 --> 00:54:24,200
Nothing, only ..

858
00:54:25,987 --> 00:54:28,076
Well, it's all happened
so quickly you know.

859
00:54:28,501 --> 00:54:31,617
Being told about doing the play.
And you wanting to marry me.

860
00:54:32,316 --> 00:54:33,127
You see.

861
00:54:34,960 --> 00:54:36,585
It would ruin your career, Don.

862
00:54:37,028 --> 00:54:39,153
You are society. I am theater.
They just don't mix.

863
00:54:39,401 --> 00:54:40,663
There is still marriage.

864
00:54:41,947 --> 00:54:43,051
Yes, I know. But ..

865
00:54:44,012 --> 00:54:45,456
Let's not talk about it just now.

866
00:54:46,489 --> 00:54:47,376
Think, Don.

867
00:54:48,164 --> 00:54:50,818
Going on the stage for the first
time in two years to play for you ..

868
00:54:51,107 --> 00:54:52,418
Your career and mine.

869
00:54:53,154 --> 00:54:55,718
Our lives, our success,
depending on one performance.

870
00:54:56,897 --> 00:54:59,116
When the lights go out
and that curtain goes up ..

871
00:54:59,580 --> 00:55:01,051
Don, that's being alive.

872
00:55:01,662 --> 00:55:03,990
I love you. I love you for
bringing me back to life.

873
00:55:04,876 --> 00:55:06,980
Are you going back to town tonight?
- Right away.

874
00:55:07,484 --> 00:55:08,757
I'm going with you.
- Why?

875
00:55:09,189 --> 00:55:10,624
To leave two years behind.

876
00:55:13,796 --> 00:55:14,682
Faster.

877
00:55:17,723 --> 00:55:18,452
Faster.

878
00:55:33,981 --> 00:55:37,227
So that's all it's been to you, Charles.
Just a shipboard romance.

879
00:55:37,704 --> 00:55:38,966
No it wasn't.
- Oh yes.

880
00:55:39,688 --> 00:55:44,194
Just a man telling a woman that the moon
and ocean aren't half as lovely as she.

881
00:55:44,968 --> 00:55:47,116
Swearing devotion, eternal as the tides.

882
00:55:47,514 --> 00:55:48,955
Sweeping the girl off her feet.

883
00:55:49,579 --> 00:55:50,651
All to be forgotten.

884
00:55:52,547 --> 00:55:53,992
That isn't what it's meant to me.

885
00:55:54,672 --> 00:55:56,539
No Charles. It has meant far more.

886
00:55:57,695 --> 00:56:00,652
Your every word, your every
kiss, your every caress.

887
00:56:01,570 --> 00:56:02,563
I've treasured.

888
00:56:03,635 --> 00:56:06,819
Because I've always pretended they
belong to the man I really love.

889
00:56:10,704 --> 00:56:12,385
Now that's something for you to forget.

890
00:56:13,305 --> 00:56:14,207
If you can.

891
00:56:15,648 --> 00:56:16,491
That's fine.

892
00:56:16,984 --> 00:56:18,201
How about it, Miss Heath?

893
00:56:18,404 --> 00:56:20,116
Too tired to go through
that scene again?

894
00:56:20,319 --> 00:56:21,333
No, I'd love to.

895
00:56:22,407 --> 00:56:24,593
I'm sorry .. I've got to beg off.

896
00:56:25,321 --> 00:56:26,162
I'm all in.

897
00:56:26,853 --> 00:56:28,573
You've got too much vitality for me.

898
00:56:29,008 --> 00:56:31,142
And for me too .. we'll call it off.

899
00:56:31,533 --> 00:56:34,457
No rehearsal tomorrow. And we'll run
through it again at 10 o'clock Monday.

900
00:56:34,756 --> 00:56:36,801
I don't like to work on the
day of the night we open.

901
00:56:37,004 --> 00:56:39,149
But there's some things I
must change .. that's all.

902
00:56:40,009 --> 00:56:41,025
Alright boys.

903
00:56:44,619 --> 00:56:47,303
Give me a cigarette.
- Sure .. what do you think?

904
00:56:47,510 --> 00:56:49,669
I've spent a fortune and
misspent a life in the theater.

905
00:56:50,026 --> 00:56:52,292
But this is the only time on
the eve of a dress rehearsal ..

906
00:56:52,503 --> 00:56:55,383
I have nerve enough to say I had a hit.
- You're pretty positive.

907
00:56:55,587 --> 00:56:57,880
So positive that I'll buy your
piece of it for $100,000.

908
00:56:58,154 --> 00:57:02,570
Oh no. Here's one angel who isn't afraid
to tread. I'm as certain as you are.

909
00:57:03,778 --> 00:57:04,955
Isn't she magnificent?

910
00:57:05,210 --> 00:57:07,702
Even in rehearsal, it's the greatest
performance I've ever seen.

911
00:57:08,168 --> 00:57:09,612
With the stimulus of an audience.

912
00:57:09,933 --> 00:57:12,065
Monday night ought to make
her immortal in the theater.

913
00:57:12,666 --> 00:57:13,793
What about that jinx?

914
00:57:14,532 --> 00:57:16,644
Jonah himself couldn't
jinx a talent like that.

915
00:57:16,915 --> 00:57:17,644
Like it?

916
00:57:18,064 --> 00:57:20,449
It's alright I guess.
Needs a lot of work though.

917
00:57:20,923 --> 00:57:24,172
You know darling, if I could get away to
the country and go over this on Sunday.

918
00:57:24,375 --> 00:57:26,793
I think I'd get a better perspective.
Can you run me down tonight?

919
00:57:27,047 --> 00:57:29,669
Certainly. Not a bad idea.
We'd better get under way.

920
00:57:29,872 --> 00:57:31,900
I want to stop by my apartment
to get my clothes.

921
00:57:32,103 --> 00:57:33,147
Alright. Goodnight.

922
00:57:33,387 --> 00:57:36,111
Goodnight, and keep her out of
the poison ivy and the fresh air.

923
00:57:36,420 --> 00:57:38,063
I don't want her to open in a whisper.

924
00:57:43,954 --> 00:57:44,779
Darling.

925
00:57:48,328 --> 00:57:49,906
We can't go on like this.

926
00:57:50,392 --> 00:57:52,409
I could .. forever.

927
00:57:52,612 --> 00:57:54,586
Don't be evasive, Joyce.
You know what I mean.

928
00:57:56,045 --> 00:57:57,007
Getting married?

929
00:57:58,247 --> 00:57:59,026
Well ..

930
00:57:59,900 --> 00:58:01,503
Of course. Sometime, darling.

931
00:58:01,947 --> 00:58:03,284
But right now there is the ..

932
00:58:03,575 --> 00:58:05,277
The show to think of.
- Look here, Joyce.

933
00:58:05,481 --> 00:58:07,520
You always find some reason
to change the subject.

934
00:58:08,058 --> 00:58:09,962
Tell me the truth.
Why are you putting me off?

935
00:58:10,518 --> 00:58:11,936
Don't be so intense, Don.

936
00:58:12,856 --> 00:58:14,815
You know I love you and
that there is no-one else.

937
00:58:15,224 --> 00:58:16,240
Isn't that enough?

938
00:58:16,443 --> 00:58:18,988
No, it's not enough. What's the matter?
Are you afraid to marry me?

939
00:58:19,688 --> 00:58:22,072
Afraid? Why should I be?

940
00:58:22,310 --> 00:58:25,263
I don't know, unless you think marriage
will make me a bit harder to get rid of.

941
00:58:25,637 --> 00:58:26,883
Don't say that Don. Don't.

942
00:58:27,599 --> 00:58:31,103
That night you asked me a month ago.
I said I couldn't promise you tomorrows.

943
00:58:31,620 --> 00:58:32,568
I can now.

944
00:58:33,226 --> 00:58:35,122
I love you enough to
give them all to you.

945
00:58:35,703 --> 00:58:37,033
At least as many as you want.

946
00:58:37,236 --> 00:58:39,569
Then we'll be married right after
the opening on Monday night.

947
00:58:41,301 --> 00:58:42,138
So soon?

948
00:58:42,409 --> 00:58:44,707
If you meant what you said just
now that wouldn't seem soon.

949
00:58:45,641 --> 00:58:47,556
It's not that, Don. Only ..
- Only what?

950
00:58:47,882 --> 00:58:48,526
Well.

951
00:58:49,049 --> 00:58:51,152
Marriage seems to make such
an issue out of everything.

952
00:58:51,742 --> 00:58:53,267
Why can't we wait a while?
- No.

953
00:58:53,470 --> 00:58:56,008
I'm not going to trail around after
you like a stage-door Johnny.

954
00:58:56,211 --> 00:58:58,818
And make a sap out of myself
waiting for you to get out of a mood.

955
00:58:59,291 --> 00:59:01,766
I want you .. but I'm through begging.

956
00:59:03,496 --> 00:59:05,029
It's either Monday night or never.

957
00:59:06,999 --> 00:59:08,314
Well of course, darling.

958
00:59:09,365 --> 00:59:10,098
Alright.

959
00:59:10,389 --> 00:59:12,708
I'll marry you Monday,
right after the show.

960
00:59:13,413 --> 00:59:15,370
We'll go down to the
park for one glorious day ..

961
00:59:15,573 --> 00:59:18,513
And I hope it rains and washes the
bridge and the road and everything away.

962
00:59:18,817 --> 00:59:20,216
So we'll be marooned forever.

963
00:59:20,732 --> 00:59:22,667
Put your arms around me
and tell me you love me.

964
00:59:23,098 --> 00:59:25,707
Look, Joyce. You're almost hysterical.
What's the matter?

965
00:59:26,071 --> 00:59:29,413
Oh nothing. Excitement, nerves.
Worrying about the show.

966
00:59:29,723 --> 00:59:33,066
Listen, I've changed my mind.
I'm very tired from rehearsing.

967
00:59:33,329 --> 00:59:35,892
I'd rather go to the country alone.
Would you lend me your car?

968
00:59:36,599 --> 00:59:39,342
Sure. If you want. But I'd hate to
have you driving alone at night.

969
00:59:39,690 --> 00:59:40,642
Don't be silly.

970
00:59:40,967 --> 00:59:43,822
Now be a good boy, and
go now or you'll see me cry.

971
00:59:46,563 --> 00:59:49,042
Hey, what's the matter?
- Nothing I tell you, but stage fright.

972
00:59:49,277 --> 00:59:51,080
Go on now, there is
always a taxi out front.

973
00:59:51,692 --> 00:59:55,369
I can see the old southern hospitality
and the artistic temperament don't mix.

974
00:59:55,836 --> 00:59:59,366
Goodnight, drive carefully and
leave the jitters down there.

975
01:00:18,406 --> 01:00:21,670
I got your bag packed for you, honey.
- Well, put it down and get out of here.

976
01:00:22,256 --> 01:00:23,122
Yes, ma'am.

977
01:01:29,252 --> 01:01:30,050
Joyce.

978
01:01:31,327 --> 01:01:33,591
I hoped you'd come
like this so many times.

979
01:01:35,055 --> 01:01:36,961
And you have, haven't you?
- Yes.

980
01:01:37,618 --> 01:01:38,461
On business.

981
01:01:39,267 --> 01:01:40,033
Come in.

982
01:01:47,110 --> 01:01:48,839
I rather hate to have
you see my quarters.

983
01:01:49,042 --> 01:01:51,685
Spare yourself any embarrassment.
I didn't come here out of curiosity.

984
01:01:52,521 --> 01:01:54,107
You'll find this one more comfortable.

985
01:01:54,310 --> 01:01:56,614
I shan't be here long enough
to find this one uncomfortable.

986
01:01:59,702 --> 01:02:00,488
Cigarette?

987
01:02:01,109 --> 01:02:01,981
No thank you.

988
01:02:18,774 --> 01:02:21,168
You still hate me, don't you?
- No, Gordon. I don't.

989
01:02:22,076 --> 01:02:23,692
There is an element of respect in hate.

990
01:02:24,029 --> 01:02:25,817
The only feeling I have
for you is contempt.

991
01:02:27,460 --> 01:02:28,618
You are very fortunate.

992
01:02:29,413 --> 01:02:32,594
Contempt is much easier to carry in your
heart than a love you can't destroy.

993
01:02:36,048 --> 01:02:37,492
You do love me, don't you Gordon?

994
01:02:39,267 --> 01:02:41,873
When a man ruins his life for something,
it's liable to be pretty real.

995
01:02:44,636 --> 01:02:47,258
I'm a bookkeeper now, Joyce.
In a company I used to own.

996
01:02:49,327 --> 01:02:50,886
The worst of it is, I can't hate you.

997
01:02:51,760 --> 01:02:53,413
I don't suppose you can understand that.

998
01:02:53,984 --> 01:02:55,779
I never could before. I do now.

999
01:02:57,566 --> 01:03:00,052
You see, I loved somebody
that way too, Gordon.

1000
01:03:01,261 --> 01:03:02,219
Heaven help you.

1001
01:03:02,793 --> 01:03:05,090
Heaven help me if .. if you won't.

1002
01:03:07,764 --> 01:03:09,046
You want me to divorce you?

1003
01:03:09,382 --> 01:03:10,403
Oh yes, Gordon.

1004
01:03:11,319 --> 01:03:13,895
I've told you time and
time again that I won't.

1005
01:03:14,700 --> 01:03:15,669
You are my wife.

1006
01:03:16,292 --> 01:03:18,108
Something you will never
be to any other man.

1007
01:03:19,303 --> 01:03:22,773
Being your husband is the only thing
I've got left and I <i>won't</i> lose it.

1008
01:03:25,074 --> 01:03:26,839
You'll be my wife until the day I die.

1009
01:03:27,838 --> 01:03:29,122
Then <i>I'll</i> divorce <i>you</i>.

1010
01:03:30,286 --> 01:03:31,277
You can't, Joyce.

1011
01:03:32,478 --> 01:03:34,294
You haven't any grounds.
You never will have.

1012
01:03:43,039 --> 01:03:43,880
Gordon.

1013
01:03:44,579 --> 01:03:47,034
I know I've ruined your happiness,
but don't ruin mine.

1014
01:03:47,440 --> 01:03:49,416
If it's revenge you want,
I'll give it to you.

1015
01:03:49,686 --> 01:03:52,405
I'll beg, I'll crawl. I'll do
anything. Anything.

1016
01:03:52,923 --> 01:03:53,648
Gordon.

1017
01:03:54,304 --> 01:03:55,416
Gordon, look at me.

1018
01:03:55,949 --> 01:03:57,679
If you want to humiliate me,
you know how.

1019
01:03:57,933 --> 01:04:00,591
But set me free, give me my
one chance of happiness.

1020
01:04:01,282 --> 01:04:02,314
Please Gordon.

1021
01:04:03,170 --> 01:04:04,372
Please, please!

1022
01:04:06,527 --> 01:04:09,117
Oh you cheap, petty bookkeeper, you.

1023
01:04:09,838 --> 01:04:14,152
Every time I think of those sticky hands
of yours touching me it makes me sick.

1024
01:04:14,687 --> 01:04:15,731
'Sick' do you hear?

1025
01:04:16,306 --> 01:04:18,794
You are everything that's
repulsive to me. Your wife.

1026
01:04:19,338 --> 01:04:22,154
I've never been a wife to you,
you poor, simpering fool.

1027
01:04:22,477 --> 01:04:25,755
If you had any pride, if you were a
man, instead of a drooling milksop.

1028
01:04:26,144 --> 01:04:28,818
You'd throw me out and be ashamed
to admit you ever married me.

1029
01:04:33,559 --> 01:04:35,782
I guess I'm better protected
against you than I used to be.

1030
01:04:40,685 --> 01:04:42,691
Neither that, nor what
you said, seemed to hurt.

1031
01:04:43,720 --> 01:04:44,486
Gordon.

1032
01:04:46,243 --> 01:04:48,218
Gordon .. you <i>can't</i> still love me.

1033
01:04:49,190 --> 01:04:50,436
When you know how I feel.

1034
01:04:51,743 --> 01:04:52,644
Yes, I do.

1035
01:04:53,365 --> 01:04:54,574
And .. and you ..?

1036
01:04:55,518 --> 01:04:57,470
And I won't divorce you .. no.

1037
01:05:15,936 --> 01:05:16,779
Gordon.

1038
01:05:18,404 --> 01:05:20,919
Gordon, I guess we are
ordained never to be happy.

1039
01:05:21,530 --> 01:05:24,516
So perhaps it would be better to make
the best of what we have and ..

1040
01:05:25,305 --> 01:05:27,174
To try and find contentment together.

1041
01:05:28,441 --> 01:05:30,901
That's all I'd ask, Joyce .. ever.

1042
01:05:32,313 --> 01:05:34,304
I'm going down to the
country over the weekend.

1043
01:05:35,468 --> 01:05:36,633
Come along if you like.

1044
01:05:38,342 --> 01:05:39,356
May I, Joyce?

1045
01:05:40,257 --> 01:05:41,112
May I?

1046
01:05:52,683 --> 01:05:53,641
Gordon.

1047
01:05:54,271 --> 01:05:56,771
Would nothing in the world
induce you to divorce me?

1048
01:05:57,867 --> 01:05:58,693
Nothing.

1049
01:05:59,163 --> 01:06:01,360
Not even to save your life?
- No.

1050
01:06:02,346 --> 01:06:04,530
Then we're going to settle
this thing once and for all.

1051
01:06:04,921 --> 01:06:06,686
If I can't have him, I'd rather be dead.

1052
01:06:07,343 --> 01:06:09,972
It's going to be your life or mine.
- Good.

1053
01:06:11,093 --> 01:06:13,956
We're coming to a tree in the
middle of the road. We're taking it.

1054
01:06:14,323 --> 01:06:15,900
If you're killed, I'll be free.

1055
01:06:16,243 --> 01:06:17,980
If I'm killed, it really doesn't matter.

1056
01:06:18,271 --> 01:06:20,093
If we both die .. good riddance.

1057
01:06:20,647 --> 01:06:21,290
Good.

1058
01:06:21,629 --> 01:06:24,174
You've taken everything but my life.
I don't want that without you.

1059
01:06:24,647 --> 01:06:26,102
Go ahead .. crash it.

1060
01:06:37,712 --> 01:06:39,136
Well, I heard a crash.

1061
01:06:39,708 --> 01:06:40,852
And I came a-running.

1062
01:06:41,389 --> 01:06:44,543
Then I saw Miss Heath with this fellow.
And that's all I know.

1063
01:06:45,122 --> 01:06:47,662
I wonder how badly
the little thing is hurt.

1064
01:06:47,982 --> 01:06:49,508
How do you know it was Joyce Heath?

1065
01:06:49,825 --> 01:06:52,171
Well, she's been staying
at Mr Bellows' farm.

1066
01:06:52,656 --> 01:06:54,827
I ought to know. I'm his housekeeper.

1067
01:06:55,228 --> 01:06:57,440
Mr Bellows? You mean
Donald Bellows the architect?

1068
01:06:57,645 --> 01:06:58,828
That's who I mean.

1069
01:06:59,204 --> 01:07:01,580
And if you want to know more
you'd better ask him yourself.

1070
01:07:01,927 --> 01:07:03,610
He should be here by now. I phoned.

1071
01:07:03,851 --> 01:07:06,171
Yeah thanks.
It may be a good idea to ask.

1072
01:07:12,733 --> 01:07:15,588
Listen, I need First Aid.
I'm a reporter, I got a lead.

1073
01:07:15,879 --> 01:07:19,071
I don't want to use the payphone
because of the other reporters, so ..

1074
01:07:19,447 --> 01:07:21,875
Can I use yours?
- I suppose so.

1075
01:07:29,580 --> 01:07:30,923
Another Florence Nightingale.

1076
01:07:31,393 --> 01:07:32,623
Hello. Give me Rewrite.

1077
01:07:33,890 --> 01:07:34,579
Eddie?

1078
01:07:34,782 --> 01:07:37,428
Listen, get this and don't squeeze it
because it will squirt in your eyes.

1079
01:07:38,350 --> 01:07:39,319
Yeah, juicy.

1080
01:07:39,863 --> 01:07:43,407
Joyce Heath who's opening a new show on
Monday was hurt in an auto accident.

1081
01:07:44,089 --> 01:07:45,970
With her was an, as yet,
unidentified man.

1082
01:07:46,363 --> 01:07:49,003
The housekeeper for Don Bellows,
socialite and architect.

1083
01:07:49,396 --> 01:07:51,518
Just admitted Joyce had
been living at his farm.

1084
01:07:52,457 --> 01:07:55,608
Bellows recently broke his engagement to
Gail Armitage of the 'Utter Armitages'.

1085
01:07:56,129 --> 01:07:58,144
Yeah. Better check that
last and I'll call you back.

1086
01:07:58,347 --> 01:08:01,219
And get your bucket and spade ready,
as I think we'll dish up some dirt.

1087
01:08:01,765 --> 01:08:02,554
Okay.

1088
01:08:06,497 --> 01:08:09,727
Well .. it's better than collecting
garbage. It's not so heavy.

1089
01:08:14,319 --> 01:08:15,485
Pardon me.
- Yes?

1090
01:08:15,688 --> 01:08:16,818
I'm Donald Bellows.

1091
01:08:17,194 --> 01:08:19,222
What about Miss Heath?
It isn't serious, is it?

1092
01:08:19,513 --> 01:08:20,156
Well.

1093
01:08:20,983 --> 01:08:22,657
There's the Doctor now. Doctor.

1094
01:08:24,064 --> 01:08:25,850
Doctor, this is Mr Bellows
about Miss Heath.

1095
01:08:26,053 --> 01:08:27,673
How is she?
- Badly shaken up.

1096
01:08:28,008 --> 01:08:30,604
Suffering from shock and
a very slight concussion.

1097
01:08:31,191 --> 01:08:32,981
She may be on her feet
in a couple of weeks.

1098
01:08:33,497 --> 01:08:35,328
The man however, is very seriously hurt.

1099
01:08:36,014 --> 01:08:38,192
It may be more than a year
before he'll be able to walk.

1100
01:08:38,897 --> 01:08:40,587
What man?
- Gordon Heath.

1101
01:08:42,202 --> 01:08:43,244
Gordon Heath?

1102
01:08:43,882 --> 01:08:45,629
Yes. He's been identified
as her husband.

1103
01:08:46,855 --> 01:08:47,719
Her husband?

1104
01:08:48,048 --> 01:08:50,700
Mrs Heath is conscious if you would
care to see her for a few minutes.

1105
01:08:51,109 --> 01:08:52,546
No, I don't want to see her.

1106
01:08:54,470 --> 01:08:56,746
Please see they both
get every possible care.

1107
01:08:57,706 --> 01:08:59,180
Anything. I'll be responsible.

1108
01:09:01,424 --> 01:09:03,261
I think you just handed him one, Doc.

1109
01:09:03,681 --> 01:09:05,366
It will sure look swell in print.

1110
01:09:23,433 --> 01:09:24,307
[ Telephone ]

1111
01:09:25,912 --> 01:09:26,564
Yes?

1112
01:09:27,630 --> 01:09:28,588
Oh yes, Don.

1113
01:09:29,443 --> 01:09:30,801
We've got to open without her.

1114
01:09:31,578 --> 01:09:32,629
What else can I do?

1115
01:09:33,540 --> 01:09:34,583
The understudy.

1116
01:09:34,808 --> 01:09:37,437
And she'll put the show right back
on the truck for Keynes warehouse.

1117
01:09:38,489 --> 01:09:41,785
Yes, she's jinxed you out of $80,000,
me out of the best show I ever had.

1118
01:09:42,226 --> 01:09:46,010
And herself out of a performance that
would make her a great American actress.

1119
01:09:46,958 --> 01:09:48,019
Sorry, old boy.

1120
01:09:50,601 --> 01:09:51,922
[ Door knocks ]

1121
01:09:53,179 --> 01:09:53,940
Yes?

1122
01:09:54,954 --> 01:09:56,325
Mr Elmont is here.

1123
01:09:59,752 --> 01:10:02,010
You got here in a hurry.
- It's important.

1124
01:10:02,723 --> 01:10:03,372
Yes?

1125
01:10:03,672 --> 01:10:04,507
Bellows.

1126
01:10:05,475 --> 01:10:06,982
We're unable to make the loan.

1127
01:10:09,207 --> 01:10:10,203
Not make it?

1128
01:10:10,719 --> 01:10:12,457
Why, it's almost a million dollars.

1129
01:10:12,748 --> 01:10:14,795
You can't sell me out.
I'm ready to start.

1130
01:10:15,367 --> 01:10:18,776
It's rumored that you put $80,000
in a show that's doomed to fail.

1131
01:10:19,518 --> 01:10:21,396
Is that correct?
- Fail?

1132
01:10:22,279 --> 01:10:23,772
Yes .. it will fail but ..

1133
01:10:24,542 --> 01:10:26,337
I can borrow that someplace else.

1134
01:10:26,891 --> 01:10:28,393
That's only a technicality.

1135
01:10:29,041 --> 01:10:31,526
We're forced to take advantage
of that technicality.

1136
01:10:31,999 --> 01:10:35,790
The board of directors, most of whom
are socially prominent .. insist on it.

1137
01:10:37,782 --> 01:10:39,888
Would you mind being
specific instead of subtle.

1138
01:10:40,268 --> 01:10:44,678
They feel the people who would've bought
the estates are prejudiced against you.

1139
01:10:45,401 --> 01:10:47,463
In other words, they don't
think you can sell them.

1140
01:10:48,070 --> 01:10:49,586
Because they're going to stop you.

1141
01:10:49,789 --> 01:10:50,537
Stop me?

1142
01:10:50,840 --> 01:10:51,704
Those snobs?

1143
01:10:52,253 --> 01:10:53,840
They won't. They or anybody else.

1144
01:10:54,669 --> 01:10:58,253
I put ten years in. Poured in everything
I ever earned into those estates.

1145
01:10:59,007 --> 01:11:00,280
I'm not going to lose them.

1146
01:11:01,420 --> 01:11:02,811
I'll get the money somewhere.

1147
01:11:03,421 --> 01:11:05,778
Well .. I hope you do.

1148
01:11:06,820 --> 01:11:08,084
But I don't think you can.

1149
01:11:12,469 --> 01:11:15,248
Well, Miss Seals. Let's have the
rest of the unfinished business.

1150
01:11:15,919 --> 01:11:17,606
The Roma Cement Company called.

1151
01:11:18,048 --> 01:11:20,508
Ignore it. We're not building anything.

1152
01:11:21,484 --> 01:11:23,739
Mr Darrell called and a Mr Wilson.

1153
01:11:25,035 --> 01:11:26,656
And Miss Heath from the hospital.

1154
01:11:27,163 --> 01:11:28,321
She said it was urgent.

1155
01:11:30,665 --> 01:11:33,981
Yes, I guess that does come
under 'unfinished business'.

1156
01:11:35,540 --> 01:11:37,546
Are you sure you've called
his office, his home?

1157
01:11:37,786 --> 01:11:41,162
Yes dear, don't worry.
Everything will be alright.

1158
01:11:41,417 --> 01:11:42,804
It's not, I tell you. It's not.

1159
01:11:43,007 --> 01:11:45,319
He couldn't let me lie here
like this unless he hated me.

1160
01:11:48,775 --> 01:11:49,481
Don.

1161
01:11:50,887 --> 01:11:52,793
Why have you waited so
long to come and see me?

1162
01:11:59,728 --> 01:12:01,115
You blame me for what happened.

1163
01:12:01,546 --> 01:12:02,635
I knew you would.

1164
01:12:03,264 --> 01:12:04,550
That's why you didn't come.

1165
01:12:05,340 --> 01:12:06,812
Yes, I blame you.

1166
01:12:08,020 --> 01:12:09,452
Don't say that, Don. Don't.

1167
01:12:10,184 --> 01:12:12,521
It's the jinx. I warned you.

1168
01:12:12,992 --> 01:12:14,489
I can't help it. I can't.

1169
01:12:16,118 --> 01:12:18,221
You mean you can't help
being rotten and selfish.

1170
01:12:19,235 --> 01:12:23,523
You'd do anything to get your own desire
and go on, leaving someone else to pay.

1171
01:12:24,386 --> 01:12:26,067
That's the jinx you put on people.

1172
01:12:28,612 --> 01:12:30,501
I was willing to sacrifice
my life for you.

1173
01:12:31,426 --> 01:12:32,525
Is that selfishness?

1174
01:12:33,539 --> 01:12:36,897
Yes, as you were afraid to risk losing
me by telling me you had a husband.

1175
01:12:37,152 --> 01:12:39,218
So, instead you lied and ruined me.

1176
01:12:40,113 --> 01:12:42,347
And your husband.
What it's cost him to love you.

1177
01:12:42,986 --> 01:12:45,819
You never paid for any happiness
in your whole life. You owe for it.

1178
01:12:46,245 --> 01:12:47,822
It cost everybody else but you.

1179
01:12:50,151 --> 01:12:51,540
I can't afford any more.

1180
01:12:52,860 --> 01:12:54,075
There's one thing I know.

1181
01:12:54,299 --> 01:12:56,917
If you'll ever be anything <i>but </i> a jinx
you'd better start paying off.

1182
01:12:57,141 --> 01:12:59,130
Because you're in debt
for the rest of your life.

1183
01:13:32,739 --> 01:13:33,687
Mrs Heath.

1184
01:13:38,143 --> 01:13:39,616
I was just in to see your husband.

1185
01:13:39,819 --> 01:13:41,432
He's been inquiring about you.

1186
01:13:42,771 --> 01:13:43,762
My husband.

1187
01:13:46,661 --> 01:13:47,734
Yes. My husband.

1188
01:13:50,478 --> 01:13:51,558
I must get up today.

1189
01:13:52,065 --> 01:13:53,896
But you can't. It's much too soon.

1190
01:13:55,670 --> 01:13:58,243
I must .. I've got some debts to pay.

1191
01:14:01,133 --> 01:14:02,349
Of course you know.

1192
01:14:02,762 --> 01:14:05,297
To reopen a play that's failed
and make a success of it.

1193
01:14:05,668 --> 01:14:08,124
Is next to impossible.
- The play wasn't a failure.

1194
01:14:08,616 --> 01:14:10,313
The only failure was mine to appear.

1195
01:14:10,932 --> 01:14:12,365
I can make that play a success.

1196
01:14:12,763 --> 01:14:14,181
You're quite confident?

1197
01:14:15,721 --> 01:14:17,231
More than confident. I'm positive.

1198
01:14:18,346 --> 01:14:19,032
Why?

1199
01:14:19,717 --> 01:14:21,304
Four very distinct reasons.

1200
01:14:22,008 --> 01:14:24,865
Any one of them so important to
me that it makes failure impossible.

1201
01:14:26,074 --> 01:14:28,254
First, I'm the only actress
suited to that part.

1202
01:14:29,708 --> 01:14:31,723
Second. Don must get his money back.

1203
01:14:33,127 --> 01:14:36,112
Third, I have a husband who's
injured for life because of me.

1204
01:14:37,333 --> 01:14:38,526
I must support him.

1205
01:14:39,538 --> 01:14:41,244
And last but most important.

1206
01:14:41,989 --> 01:14:43,664
I found out how to break my jinx.

1207
01:14:44,669 --> 01:14:45,713
By paying my debts.

1208
01:14:48,396 --> 01:14:50,529
Are you strong enough to
start rehearsing Monday?

1209
01:14:52,445 --> 01:14:53,093
Yes.

1210
01:14:55,853 --> 01:14:56,915
I've got to be.

1211
01:14:58,033 --> 01:14:59,535
Monday morning at ten, then.

1212
01:14:59,751 --> 01:15:00,880
Monday morning at ten.

1213
01:15:01,685 --> 01:15:02,869
Thanks so much.

1214
01:15:25,565 --> 01:15:26,834
Pardon the coincidence.

1215
01:15:27,274 --> 01:15:28,547
It's no coincidence, Joyce.

1216
01:15:28,750 --> 01:15:30,903
I've been looking for you.
They told me you'd come here.

1217
01:15:31,476 --> 01:15:32,823
I want to talk to you.

1218
01:15:33,107 --> 01:15:35,172
You were very frank the
last time we talked together.

1219
01:15:36,064 --> 01:15:37,604
Everything I said was the truth.

1220
01:15:42,824 --> 01:15:45,194
Let me be just as frank
and just as honest.

1221
01:15:47,145 --> 01:15:48,687
You're no longer important to me.

1222
01:15:50,180 --> 01:15:52,103
Your importance ended
when the show closed.

1223
01:15:53,549 --> 01:15:55,802
You mean, I was just a means to an end?

1224
01:15:56,732 --> 01:15:58,041
Why not call it that?

1225
01:16:00,792 --> 01:16:02,970
How cheap.
- No, I ..

1226
01:16:04,717 --> 01:16:05,933
I'm rather expensive.

1227
01:16:06,816 --> 01:16:08,110
Remember what it cost you.

1228
01:16:27,873 --> 01:16:28,751
